	<text>
		<body>
			<div type="entry">
				<pb facs="https://leaf.bucknell.edu/sites/default/files/2026-01/diary70.jpg"/>
				<dateline><date>Monday 26</date>.</dateline>
				<p>It has been a succession of rainy days. We have a nice cozy time indoors, but
					cant help thinking of <orgName>McClellan’s army</orgName>: it must be dreadful
					in that low swampy country. <persName key="Jacob G. Beaver"
						ref="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BucknellDSC/jmlinn/refs/heads/main/jmlinn_personography.xml#jmlper003"
						>Lt Beaver</persName> and I strolled around town after morning drill. We saw
					two of<persName key="Em French"
						ref="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BucknellDSC/jmlinn/refs/heads/main/jmlinn_personography.xml#jmlper029"
						> Em French’s</persName> whores &amp; several from the crow-nest. <persName
						key="George Shorkley"
						ref="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BucknellDSC/jmlinn/refs/heads/main/jmlinn_personography.xml#jmlper002"
						>Shorkley’s</persName> &amp; my visit to those celebrated places is
					unrecorded, but not unremembered. I never had such fun as the crow-nest
					afforded. There are three ladies that live down in a house with a porch in front
					that <persName key="Jacob G. Beaver"
						ref="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BucknellDSC/jmlinn/refs/heads/main/jmlinn_personography.xml#jmlper003"
						>Beaver</persName> and I take occasion to pass every day - they are the only
					ladies we have seen in town. On Saturday, we met a <persName key="Col. Pollack"
						ref="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BucknellDSC/jmlinn/refs/heads/main/jmlinn_personography.xml#jmlper198"
						> Pollock</persName> from <placeName key="Reading"
						ref="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BucknellDSC/jmlinn/refs/heads/main/jmlinn_gazetteer.xml#linnpl074"
						>Reading, </placeName>cousin of <persName>John’s wife</persName> - a
					corporal in one of the<orgName> 4 companies of the 48th,</orgName> which had
					been left at <placeName key="Cape Hatteras"
						ref="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BucknellDSC/jmlinn/refs/heads/main/jmlinn_gazetteer.xml#linnp0l13"
						>Hatteras</placeName>, and came on here the other day. I met him
						in<placeName key="Philadelphia"
						ref="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BucknellDSC/jmlinn/refs/heads/main/jmlinn_gazetteer.xml#linnpl069"
						> Philadelphia</placeName> when <persName key="John Morris"
						ref="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BucknellDSC/jmlinn/refs/heads/main/jmlinn_personography.xml#jmlper057"
						>Morris</persName> &amp; I were there, and little dreamed of meeting him
					here. I might have seen him at <placeName key="Cape Hatteras"
						ref="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BucknellDSC/jmlinn/refs/heads/main/jmlinn_gazetteer.xml#linnp0l13"
						>Hatteras</placeName> had I taken the trouble to go to <placeName>Merifield
					</placeName>but I did not know he was there. </p>
			</div>
		</body>
	</text>
